  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*:  bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: when you switching between chats with several days history, messages from yesterday and earlier can be overlapping between different chats.\r\nBlocked by  status-im/react-native-desktop#253.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nno overlapping\r\n\r\n### Actual result:\r\n\"Today\" disappears\r\nmessages from \"Yesterday\" are overlapping between chats\r\n<img width=\"325\" alt=\"m1\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/42038824-895cf41c-7af4-11e8-814b-8a645248bee4.png\">\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\nSteps:\r\n*Requirements:* have 1-1 and public chat with history more than 1 day\r\n\r\n1) log in\r\n2) switch between chats with history>1 day (i.e. \"Today\" and \"Yesterday\")\r\n3) check history in 1-1 chat\r\n\r\n### Expected result: \r\nno overlapping\r\n\r\n* Video: http://take.ms/yMabF\r\n* Log: [StatusIm.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2145576/StatusIm.log)\r\n\r\n**NOTE**: if you switch to chat with \"Today\" messages only, and then to chat with several days history - you cannot see an issue until you switch to another chat with several days history.\r\n\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://api.monosnap.com/rpc/file/download?id=O9DQQCeb6jB67iWQlGsftA45c0ISpL&type=preview\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div>Monosnap screenshot tool</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://monosnap.com/file/O9DQQCeb6jB67iWQlGsftA45c0ISpL\">File \"screencast 2018-06-28 16-16-15.mp4\"</a></strong></div><div>Monosnap â€” the best tool to take & share your screenshots.</div></blockquote>",
